# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EMBFinder — Environment Configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to .env before running:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# The Go backend loads .env automatically from the current directory
# and from its parent directory (so running from go-server/ still works).
# All variables are optional — commented-out values show the built-in default.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── Runtime mode ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# development : verbose logs, data/ subfolder for the database
# production  : minimal logs, platform config directory for the database
#               Linux:   ~/.config/EMBFinder/embfinder.db
#               macOS:   ~/Library/Application Support/EMBFinder/embfinder.db
#               Windows: %APPDATA%\EMBFinder\embfinder.db
#
MODE=development


# ── Go backend (port 8765) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HOST and PORT control where the HTTP server listens.
# Set HOST=0.0.0.0 to accept connections from other machines on the network.
# If PORT is already in use the server will find the next free port automatically.
#
# HOST=127.0.0.1
# PORT=8765


# ── AI Embedding service (port 8766) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# The Go backend talks to the Python embedder for CLIP vector generation.
# EMBEDDER_URL takes priority over EMBEDDER_HOST + EMBEDDER_PORT if set.
#
# To point at a remote GPU server:
#   EMBEDDER_URL=http://192.168.1.50:8766
#
# EMBEDDER_HOST=127.0.0.1
# EMBEDDER_PORT=8766
# EMBEDDER_URL=


# ── EMB Rendering engine (port 8767) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# The Flask service that renders .EMB files to PNG previews.
# Only needed for indexing EMB files — search still works without it.
#
# EMB_ENGINE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8767


# ── CLIP model selection ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Applies to both the Python embedder subprocess started automatically by the
# Go backend AND to a manually started embedder (passed via env).
#
# Available models (accuracy vs VRAM trade-off):
#   ViT-L-14   →  openai weights      ~1.7 GB VRAM  [default, best accuracy]
#   ViT-H-14   →  laion2b_s32b_b79k   ~3.2 GB VRAM  [highest accuracy, slower]
#   ViT-B-32   →  laion2b_s34b_b79k   ~0.6 GB VRAM  [lightweight fallback]
#
# CLIP_MODEL=ViT-L-14


# ── Database path ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Absolute or relative path to the SQLite database file.
# In development mode the default is ./data/embfinder.db (relative to the
# go-server/ directory). In production mode it uses the platform config dir.
# Override here to store the database on a specific drive or location.
#
# DB_PATH=./data/embfinder.db


# ── Desktop window ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set HEADLESS=1 to run as a plain HTTP server without the Wails desktop window.
# Useful for server deployments, Docker, or when running over SSH.
#
# HEADLESS=0


# ── Embroidery library ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by Docker Compose to mount your library into the container.
# Not read by the Go backend directly — set the scan path via the UI instead.
#
# EMB_LIB=/path/to/your/embroidery_library
